Sonu Nigam began his singing career at the age of three, when he joined his father on stage to sing Mohammad Rafi's &quot;Kya Hua Tera Wada, Wo Kasam Wo Irada.&quot; From then on, Sonu accompanied his father on his singing appearances at weddings and parties. In his teenage years, Nigam participated in several music competitions successfully. He moved to Mumbai with his father to begin his Bollywood singing career at the age of 19.[3]


